subSubSection.paragraph:
B. jeffreysii
was described from off the Hebrids (Scotland). It is cold temperate Atlantic species ranging from northernmost locations at the Lofoten islands north of the Arctic Circle, 67°30’ N (
Byrkjedal et al. 2016
) to southernmost locations from the Celtic Sea ( Miller, 1986 ) and Brittany (estuaries of rivers Morlaix and Penzé), 48°40’ N ( Le Danois 1910 ). The single recorded water temperature at collecting depth was 7.4° C (
Byrkjedal et al. 2016
).
